e a wind blow over the earth, and the waters subsided."}, {:version=>"Berean Study Bible", :text=>"But God remembered Noah and all the animals and livestock that were with him in the ark. And God sent a wind over the earth, and the waters began to subside."}, {:version=>"New American Standard Bible ", :text=>"But God remembered Noah and all the beasts and all the cattle that were with him in the ark; and God caused a wind to pass over the earth, and the water subsided."}, {:version=>"New King James Version", :text=>"Then God remembered Noah, and every living thing, and all the animals that "}, {:version=>" with him in the ark. And God made a wind to pass over the earth, and the waters subsided.", :text=>"King James Bible"}, {:version=>"And God remembered Noah, and every living thing, and all the cattle that ", :text=>" with him in the ark: and God made a wind to pass over the earth, and the waters asswaged;"}, {:version=>"Christian Standard Bible", :text=>"God remembered Noah, as well as all the wildlife and all the livestock that were with him in the ark. God caused a wind to pass over the earth, and the water began to subside."}, {:version=>"Contemporary English Version", :text=>"God did not forget about Noah and the animals with him in the boat. So God made a wind blow, and the water started going down. "}, {:version=>"Good News Translation", :text=>"God had not forgotten Noah and all the animals with him in the boat; he caused a wind to blow, and the water started going down. "}, {:version=>"Holman Christian Standard Bible", :text=>"God remembered Noah, as well as all the wildlife and all the livestock that were with him in the ark. God caused a wind to pass over the earth, and the water began to subside. "}, {:version=>"International Standard Version", :text=>"God kept Noah in mind, along with all the wildlife and livestock that were with him in the ark. God's Spirit moved throughout the earth, causing the flood waters to subside. "}, {:version=>"NET Bible", :t